results.lead_paragraph: TUNE is a bonanza month for brides and bakers. Homemade or custom-Ordered, cake and ceremony seem inevitably inter twined. "it's the personal touch that people seem to care about today, and the quality of the ingredients," Carole Spence, the proprietor of Create-a-Cake, said recently as she dispensed advice on how to bake cakes for virtually any occasion.

results.lead_paragraph: A former astronaut, John L. Swigert Jr., yesterday announced his candidacy for the United States Senate, in a bid to take the seat now held by Senator Floyd K. Haskell, Democrat of Colorado. Mr. Swigert, who is 46 years old, is a Republican now serving as executive director of the Colorado House's Committee on Science and Technology, a job which he said he'll now give up.
